28/01/2010
ATHENS, Greece -- Parliament Speaker Filippos Petsalnikos announced Wednesday (January 27th) that the legislature will elect the country's president on February 3rd.
Both Prime Minister George Papandreou of the ruling PASOK party and Antonis Samaras, leader of the conservative opposition New Democracy party, support the re-election of incumbent Karolos Papoulias, who is now running unopposed.
Papandreou met with Papoulias on Wednesday to express his support.
Under the Greek Constitution, the president is elected by parliament in three rounds.
(Kathimerini - 28/01/10;
Xinhua, ERT, MIA - 27/01/10)
